cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses neural networks and attention mechanisms to improve the performance of sentiment analysis. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses a tree-structured neural network. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it uses attention mechanisms to identify the most salient representations during the construction of the syntactic tree.
